`g "hello"` expands to `fun _ => do let s := `(a b c #[x, $(quote "hello"), z])` ; pure s`.
So, `g "hello" = fun _ => pure [x, "hello", z]`.

Therefore, `fun _ => pure [x, "hello", z] = fun _ => pure .missing`.
This implies `pure [x, "hello", z] = pure .missing`.
So, `[x, "hello", z] = .missing`.

